.TH TEST-ZH 1 "2026-01-01" "pyname" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
test-zh \- check if filenames contain Chinese characters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B test-zh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILE\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtest-zh\fR checks if filenames contain Chinese characters. It returns exit code 0 if the condition is met, 1 otherwise.
.PP
By default, it checks if any filename contains Chinese characters, and all files must match.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--full\fR
Check if filename contains only Chinese characters (and whitespace).
.TP
\fB-a\fR, \fB--all\fR
All files must match the condition (default).
.TP
\fB-1\fR, \fB--one\fR
At least one file must match the condition.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Show help message and exit.
.TP
\fB--version\fR
Show version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Check if any filename contains Chinese characters:
.RS
.PP
test-zh file1.txt 你好.txt
.RE
.PP
Check if all filenames contain only Chinese characters:
.RS
.PP
test-zh -f -a 你好.txt 世界.txt
.RE
.PP
Check if at least one filename contains Chinese characters:
.RS
.PP
test-zh -a file1.txt 你好.txt
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 if condition is met, 1 otherwise.
